design:
Replace the broken startsWith check. Proposed (3 lines):

if (location.pathname === '/') return null;
if (['/sign-in', '/sign-up', '/waitlist', '/changelog'].some(p => location.pathname.startsWith(p))) {
  return null;
}

Rationale: landing needs exact-match ('/'); other public/auth pages are fine with startsWith (no route collisions). Keeps the nav rendered on all authenticated app routes (/dashboard, /tasks/:id, /settings/*, /admin, etc.).
